Speaking about the advantages of the front strut, the following should be distinguished:

    Low chance of cracks on the body due to long service life (age defects);
    The vehicle keeps on the road much more confidently, it more accurately enters the turns, which is due to the increased level of rigidity;
    The trajectory of the car becomes clearer and more precise;
    Resistant to high loads and aggressive driving;
    Increase the stability of the car with a straight ride;
    No deformation of the body, when driving on uneven roads.

Is the spacer so useful and does it need anything at all? In general, yes. Few motorists prefer the style of driving, like racing, but why not go through the usual turn not at a speed of 50 km per hour, but at 80 km per hour (the presence of a spacer).

Regarding the disadvantages: the worst in the strut - increased damage to the car in case of an accident. If the blow is directed to the place where the spacer is installed, this will cause deformation and damage to both sides of the body. The accident may require significant financial waste (instead of repairing or replacing one side of the vehicle, you will have to replace the entire front end of the vehicle).
